name: Minotaur Labyrinth
description: Pursued by King Minos, they cut up Minos's son, and while Minos gathered his son's pieces from the sea, Theseus and Ariadne fled. King Minos blamed Daedalus for all the tragedy and as a punishment, locked Daedalus and his son Icarus inside the Labyrinth, making them prisoners for life.
